This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as it focuses on WLAN trace analysis and understanding user behavior in wireless networks. Additionally, the paper may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it investigates encounter patterns and friendship relations among users. Other possible sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SY (Systems and Control), and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the study has implications for realistic modeling of network usage and mobility patterns, and may have social and societal impacts.
